{{#> _page }}
<div class="bgimg" style="background-image: url('assets/images/documentation/screen-page.png');"
  data-stellar-background-ratio="0.5">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row align-items-center justify-content-center text-center">
      <div class="col-md-7">
        <h2 class="">Documentation</h2>
        <p class="lead mx-auto desc mb-5">Follow the steps to intercept your first request with tweak!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="site-section">
  <div style="margin: 50px;">
    <h2>Step 1 - Request setup</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 1 - Request setup" src="assets/images/documentation/step1.png" class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <ul>
          <li>Open the DevTools Network tab</li>
          <li>In the Name section, <b>select the request you want to intercept if you need to collect information about
              the request</b></li>
          <li>Open tweak and fill in <b>Configuration name</b>, <b>HTTP Method</b> and <b>Request URL</b> according to
            the
            caracteristics of
            the request you want to intercept</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Step 2 - Raw response data</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 2 - Copy the raw response data" src="assets/images/documentation/step2.png" class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <ul>
          <li><b>Copy the Raw response data</b> from the response section</li>
          <li><b>Paste the Raw response data in the json editor in tweak</b></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Step 3 - Format the response</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 3 - Format the data to make it readable" src="assets/images/documentation/step3.png"
          class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <p>In the json editor, you can <b>format the data</b> by clicking on the first icon. The data will be more
          readable and you can start tweaking the response as you need.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Step 4 - tweak the response payload</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 4 - tweak the response in the json editor" src="assets/images/documentation/step4.png"
          class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <p><b>tweak the response</b> in the json editor by adding, removing or editing existing data fields.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Step 5 - Run the extension</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 5 - Run the extension" src="assets/images/documentation/step5.png" class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <p>Go to the menu on the top left of the extension and <b>click Run</b>.</p>
        <p>By default, the extention is paused as it could interfere with the websites that you normally use.</p>
        <p>It is a good practice to keep the extention turned off when you are not using it, otherwise it would perform
          unnecessary work in the background.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Step 6 - Switch on the Request</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 6 - Switch on the Request that you want to intercept" src="assets/images/documentation/step6.png"
          class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <p><b>Switch on</b> the request(s) that you want to intercept.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Step 7 - Request intercepted!</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <img alt="Step 7 - The request was intercepted!" src="assets/images/documentation/step7.png" class="img-fluid">
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <p><b>Reproduce the event that triggers the data fetching</b>, in this example by clicking on the refresh
          button.</p>
        <p>When the request is intercepted, you will see a number near the switch in the extention. This number displays
          the amount of requests successfully intercepted.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row" style="margin: 50px;">
    <p>Do you want to try it yourself in the same application? <a href="https://tweak-target-app.herokuapp.com"
        target="_blank"><b>Here</b></a> you can access
      the website shown in these steps.</p>
  </div>
</div>
{{/ _page }}
